#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.32:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.32:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga"
msgstr "4. Situations"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: saṅgahavatthusuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.32:0.3"
msgid "32. Saṅgahasutta"
msgstr "32. Inclusion"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.32:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, saṅgahavatthūni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four ways of being inclusive."

msgctxt "an4.32:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.32:1.3"
msgid "Dānaṃ, peyyavajjaṃ, atthacariyā, samānattatā—"
msgstr "Giving, kind speech, taking care, and equality."

msgctxt "an4.32:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri saṅgahavatthūnīti."
msgstr "These are the four ways of being inclusive."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.32:2.1"
msgid "Dānañca peyyavajjañca,"
msgstr "Giving, kind speech,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:2.2"
msgid "atthacariyā ca yā idha;"
msgstr "taking care here,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:2.3"
msgid "Samānattatā ca dhammesu,"
msgstr "and equality in worldly conditions,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:2.4"
msgid "tattha tattha yathārahaṃ;"
msgstr "in each case as they deserve."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:2.5"
msgid "Ete kho saṅgahā loke,"
msgstr "These ways of being inclusive in the world"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:2.6"
msgid "rathassāṇīva yāyato."
msgstr "are like a moving chariot’s linchpin."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.32:3.1"
msgid "Ete ca saṅgahā nāssu,"
msgstr "If there were no such ways of being inclusive,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:3.2"
msgid "na mātā puttakāraṇā;"
msgstr "neither mother nor father"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:3.3"
msgid "Labhetha mānaṃ pūjaṃ vā,"
msgstr "would be respected and honored"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:3.4"
msgid "pitā vā puttakāraṇā."
msgstr "for what they’ve done for their children."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: saṅgahā → saṅgahe (aṭṭhakathāyaṃ pāṭhantaraṃ)
msgctxt "an4.32:4.1"
msgid "Yasmā ca saṅgahā ete,"
msgstr "But since these ways of being inclusive do exist,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:4.2"
msgid "samavekkhanti paṇḍitā;"
msgstr "the astute do regard them well,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:4.3"
msgid "Tasmā mahattaṃ papponti,"
msgstr "so they achieve greatness"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.32:4.4"
msgid "pāsaṃsā ca bhavanti te”ti."
msgstr "and are praised.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.32:4.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
